19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 2, Chapter 20, 1st
21 Extraordinary Session, O.S.L. 2023 (68 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
22 2357.801), is amended to read as follows:
23 Section 2357.801. A. As used in this section:
24 1. "Activities of daily living (ADL)" shall include:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4118 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 a. ambulating, which is the extent of an individual's
2 ability to move from one position to another and walk
3 independently,
4 b. feeding, which is the ability of an individual to feed
5 oneself,
6 c. dressing, which is the ability to select appropriate
7 clothes and to put the clothes on without aid,
8 d. personal hygiene, which is the ability to bathe and
9 groom oneself and maintain dental hygiene and nail and
10 hair care,
11 e. continence, which is the ability to control bladder
12 and bowel function, and
13 f. toileting, which is the ability to get to and from the
14 toilet without aid, using it appropriately, and
15 cleaning oneself;
16 2. "Eligible expenditure" shall include:
17 a. the improvement or alteration to the family
18 caregiver's or eligible family member's primary
19 residence to permit the eligible family member to live
20 in the residence and to remain mobile, safe, and
21 independent,
22 b. the family caregiver's purchase or lease of equipment,
23 including but not limited to durable medical
24 equipment, that is necessary to assist an eligible
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4118 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 family member in carrying out one or more activities
2 of daily living (ADL), and
3 c. other paid or incurred expenses by the family
4 caregiver that assist the family caregiver in
5 providing care to an eligible family member, such as
6 expenditures related to:
7 (1) hiring a home care aide,
8 (2) respite care,
9 (3) adult day care,
10 (4) personal care attendants,
11 (5) health care equipment, and
12 (6) technology.
13 The eligible expenditure must shall be directly related to assisting
14 the family caregiver in providing care to an eligible family member.
15 This includes any mileage for driving the eligible family member to
16 and from medical appointments. Calculate the estimated mileage at
17 the IRS standard rate for medical and dental expenses for the
18 applicable tax year. Eligible expenditure shall not include the
19 carrying out of general household maintenance activities such as
20 painting, plumbing, electrical repairs, or exterior maintenance;
21 3. "Eligible family member" shall mean an individual who:
22 a. is sixty-two (62) years of age or older,
23 b. requires assistance with at least two activities of
24 daily living (ADL) as certified by a licensed health
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4118 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 care provider, as defined in paragraph 1 of Section
2 3090.2 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
3 c.
4 b. qualifies as a dependent, spouse, parent, or other
5 relation by blood or marriage to the family caregiver,
6 and
7 d.
8 c. lives in a private residential home and not in an
9 assisted living center, nursing facility, or
10 residential care home; and
11 4. "Family caregiver" shall mean an individual:
12 a. providing care and support for an eligible family
13 member,
14 b. who has a federal adjusted gross income of less than
15 Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00) Seventy-five
16 Thousand Dollars ($75,000.00) for an individual and
17 less than One Hundred Thousand Dollars ($100,000.00)
18 One Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($150,000.00) for a
19 couple filing jointly, and
20 c. who has personally incurred uncompensated expenses
21 directly related to the care of an eligible family
22 member.
23 B. For taxable years beginning after December 31, 2023, there
24 shall be allowed a credit against the tax imposed pursuant to
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4118 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Sect ion 2355 of Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes in the amount of
2 fifty percent (50%) for eligible expenditures incurred by a family
3 caregiver for the care and support of an eligible family member.
4 C. The maximum allowable credit authorized by this section
5 shall be Two Thousand Dollars ($2,000.00) unless the eligible family
6 member is a veteran or has a diagnosis of dementia in which case the
7 maximum allowable credit shall be Three Thousand Dollars
8 ($3,000.00). If two or more family caregivers claim the tax credit
9 authorized by this section for the same eligible family member, the
10 maximum allowable credit shall be allocated in equal amounts between
11 each of the family caregivers.
12 D. The credit authorized by this section may shall not be used
13 to reduce the tax liability of the taxpayer to less than zero (0).
14 The credit shall not be carried over.
15 E. The total credits authorized pursuant to this section for
16 all taxpayers shall not exceed One Million Five Hundred Thousand
17 Dollars ($1,500,000.00) annually. In the event the total tax
18 credits authorized by this section exceed One Million Five Hundred
19 Thousand Dollars ($1,500,000.00) annually in any calendar year, the
20 Oklahoma Tax Commission shall permit any excess over One Million
21 Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($1,500,000.00) annually, but shall
22 factor such excess into the percentage adjustment formula for
23 subsequent years. The Oklahoma Tax Commission shall annually
24 calculate and publish by the first day of the affected year a
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4118 SFLR Page 5
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 perc entage by which the credits authorized by this section shall be
2 reduced so the total amount of credits used to offset tax does not
3 exceed One Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($1,500,000.00)
4 annually per year. The formula to be used for the percentage
5 adjustment shall be One Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars
6 ($1,500,000.00) annually divided by the credits claimed in the
7 second preceding year.
8 F. The Oklahoma Tax Commission shall promulgate rules necessary
9 to implement and administer the credit authorized by this section.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
